Definition.WordDefinition: Bottle \Bot"tle\, v. t. [imp. & p. p. {Bottled}p. pr. & vb. n. {Bottling}.] To put into bottles; to inclose in, or as in, a bottle or bottles; to keep or restrain as in a bottle; as, to bottle wine or porter; to bottle up one's wrath. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition:
Bottled \Bot"tled\, a. 1. Put into bottles; inclosed in bottles; pent up in, or as in, a bottle. [1913 Webster]
2. Having the shape of a bottle; protuberant. --Shak. [1913 Webster]
